{
  "assumptions": [
    "Traffic ~<1k/mo — all tiers sized for low-volume, cost-optimized shapes",
    "TradingView webhooks POST JSON alerts (ticker, direction, price, timestamp) to a public HTTPS endpoint",
    "Existing public dashboard (display layer) is out of scope — architecture only covers the ingest + fan-out + AI evaluation pipeline",
    "AI evaluation = a Python process that fetches OHLCV/market data, runs analysis, and writes a result record; assumed async/non-blocking relative to the webhook response",
    "No PII or regulated data — no compliance regime applied",
    "Best-effort downtime tolerance → single-AZ baseline is acceptable; no SLA commitment",
    "Idempotency key = TradingView alert ID (or timestamp+ticker hash) used for dedup",
    "Market data download in AI worker uses an external API (e.g. yfinance, Polygon) — credentials stored in Secrets Manager",
    "Evaluation results written back to the same datastore for dashboard consumption",
    "No user authentication needed on the public dashboard endpoint (read-only public data)",
    "Cost estimates are on-demand list prices for us-east-1, presented as ranges over assumed monthly volumes. They exclude the AWS Free Tier, Savings Plans, Reserved Instances, and negotiated discounts.",
    "Assumed traffic ~10k–100k requests/month, applied equally to all three tiers (tiers differ by robustness, not traffic). Set \"expected monthly visitors\" in intake to change it."
  ],
  "clarificationsUsed": [
    "Best-effort downtime tolerance → budget tier is single-AZ, no redundancy required",
    "No data sensitivity → SSE/KMS at-rest is the floor but no HIPAA/PCI regime",
    "<1k/mo visitors → Lambda + DynamoDB on-demand is idle-cost ~$0; no always-on compute needed"
  ],
  "tiers": [
